name: Drifter
desc: A jack of all trades who manipulates persistent multi-use tracks on their loss cards to empower various abilities.

name: Blink Blade
desc: A complex character who uses a system of tokens to move different speeds and use crowd control and deal damage on some rounds while be less effective on others.

name: Banner Spear
desc: A tanky damage dealer who works with allies in special formation area attacks that require allies in order to work.

name: Deathwalker
desc: A damage dealer who uses placed shadow tokens resulting from enemy deaths to do strong damage and movement effects.

name: Boneshaper
desc: A summon-based character with non-loss summons that cost HP.

name: Geminate
desc: An area attacker with two forms, each with their own separate hands; one melee-focused and one ranged-focus, who swap between them by playing specific effects

name: Brute
desc: A very simple tanky class who has a minor specialization in movement.

name: Tinkerer
desc: A healing-based support who can play losses to make up for his shortcomings in terms of damage.

name: Spellweaver
desc: A somewhat complex ranged area attacker with a unique stamina system that allows her to play losses more freely.

name: Scoundrel
desc: A high damage melee attacker who specializes in moving in and out of melee while gaining benefits from adjacent allies.

name: Cragheart
desc: A jack of all trades with a focus on area damage and obstacle use.

name: Mindthief
desc: A fairly complex melee attacker with a unique augment system who can use crowd control abilities to disable enemies.

name: Hatchet
desc: A ranged attacker who uses their favorite hatchet to do massive damage, but must retrieve it thereafter.

name: Demolitionist
desc: A melee attacker who destroys obstacles for various attacks.

name: Voidwarden
desc: An element-based control mage who can force enemies to act or grant their allies actions or other benefits.

name: Red Guard
desc: A light- and fire-base tank class who can use a specific card to let their shield cards output damage.
